OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright but cold start to the
OL,6,Fday. Cloud slowly increasing ahead of
OL,7,Fa band of patchy light rain moving
OL,8,Fsouth during the afternoon, then
OL,9,Fclearing into the evening.
OL,10,FTemperatures a little below average,
OL,11,Fand with brisk northwesterly winds.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FAny showers mostly clearing
OL,14,Fto leave clear skies for a while
OL,15,Fovernight. Cloud building later with
OL,16,Fblustery showers arriving by dawn.
OL,17,FLess cold than in recent nights, with
OL,18,Fbrisk winds.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
